+# AccessRevamp architecture
+
+## Request flow
+
+```text
+Browser
+  ├─ static HTML/CSS/JS from Netlify CDN
+  └─ same-origin /api/*
+       └─ Netlify Function
+            ├─ Supabase Auth REST
+            ├─ Supabase Data REST / RPC
+            └─ Stripe Checkout API
+
+Stripe
+  └─ signed webhook → /api/stripe/webhook → idempotent order/project sync
+
+Google Sheet
+  └─ reviewed batch + bearer token → /api/automation/reviewed-batch
+       ├─ suppression check
+       ├─ prospect + verified finding
+       ├─ keyed-hash private preview token
+       └─ outreach draft requiring staff approval
+
+Scan worker
+  └─ public GET-only navigation → screenshot + axe results + passive observations
+       └─ human review before any prospect-facing use
+```
+
+## Trust boundaries
+
+- Browser code receives only public runtime configuration. It never receives Supabase secret keys, Stripe secret keys, webhook secrets, automation tokens, or hashing secrets.
+- All customer writes pass through the same-origin function, where payload size, origin, field constraints, honeypots, and rate limits are enforced.
+- Customer sessions use `__Host-` secure, HTTP-only, SameSite cookies.
+- Staff authorization comes from a server-side allowlist or the `ar_staff` table; user-editable profile metadata is not authorization.
+- Private preview tokens are returned once and stored only as keyed hashes.
+- Stripe webhooks are verified against the unmodified raw request body before state changes.
+- The Supabase secret key is limited to the server runtime. Public/authenticated Data API grants remain minimal even though the API generally uses the secret key.
+
+## Deliberate omissions
+
+The first release has no recurring billing, browser extension, client-side Supabase SDK, autonomous prospect scraper, unreviewed email sender, tracking pixels, active vulnerability scanner, legal-compliance scorer, or custom-domain dependency. These omissions reduce cost and risk while the service validates demand.
