+# AccessRevamp
+
+**See the barrier. Preview the fix.**
+
+AccessRevamp is a service-first website accessibility and redesign studio. This monorepo contains the public website, customer account flow, private concept previews, Supabase schema, Stripe one-time checkout, a passive public-homepage scanner, and a human-review outreach queue.
+
+## Launch offers
+
+| Offer | Price | Included |
+| --- | ---: | --- |
+| AccessRevamp Snapshot | Free | One human-verified accessibility finding, one usability/design opportunity, evidence, and an expiring private first-screen concept. |
+| Homepage Reveal | **$50 one-time** | Verified homepage findings, evidence, WCAG references, a prioritized repair plan, and the complete first-screen concept. |
+| Complete Website Revamp | **$199 one-time** | One agreed small-business website revamp scope, implementation, accessibility and passive website-health review, evidence, one retest, and a practical customer-reach/growth action plan. |
+
+There is no AccessRevamp subscription and no added AccessRevamp card-processing surcharge. Stripe may show legally required tax when tax collection is correctly configured. Third-party themes, plugins, apps, hosting, licensed assets, advertising spend, custom backends, ecommerce migrations, and ongoing maintenance are outside the $199 base scope unless agreed in writing.
+
+## Repository map
+
+```text
+apps/marketing-web/             Static, semantic marketing site and client-facing pages
+apps/scan-worker/               Playwright + axe public-homepage evidence worker
+netlify/functions/              Same-origin API for Supabase Auth/data and Stripe Checkout
+packages/finding-model/         Severity, confidence, and prospect-facing evidence guards
+packages/outreach/              Draft policy, copy renderer, and scare-claim checks
+supabase/migrations/            AccessRevamp-only tables, RLS, grants, and guard triggers
+integrations/google-apps-script Review-sheet import bridge; creates drafts, never sends mail
+docs/                           Architecture, deployment, security, methodology, and operations
+scripts/                        Build, validation, preview, and local draft tooling
+templates/                      Safe placeholder review/import examples
+tests/                          Node-native unit and contract tests
+```
+
+## What is implemented
+
+- A responsive marketing site with pricing, sample report, methodology, contact, legal pages, accessibility statement, authentication screens, customer dashboard, private preview route, checkout status, and staff review queue.
+- Netlify Function endpoints for intake, contact, opt-out, Supabase Auth, session cookies, dashboard records, Stripe Checkout, signed Stripe webhooks, private previews, reviewed-batch import, and staff draft approval.
+- Fixed Stripe catalog prices of **5,000 cents** and **19,900 cents** are verified server-side before Checkout is created. The browser cannot choose an amount or price ID.
+- Supabase migrations with `ar_*` isolation, Row Level Security, explicit grants, permanent suppression records, rate-limit buckets, private storage, and a database trigger that blocks outreach state changes without human approval.
+- A passive scanner that limits itself to public HTTP(S) pages, blocks private/reserved network targets, prevents non-GET network activity, runs deterministic axe checks, records evidence, and marks every result as requiring human review.
+- A Google Sheets bridge that imports up to 20 human-reviewed prospects, creates private previews/drafts, records suppression, and can send only staff-approved rows through Gmail after independent enable switches are turned on.
+
+## Local setup
+
+Requirements: Node.js 22 and a trusted Chromium/Chrome binary for the optional scan worker.
+
+```bash
+npm ci
+npm run check
+npm run preview
+```
+
+Open `http://localhost:4173`. The static preview does not provide API functions. For full local API testing, use the Netlify CLI with values from `.env.example`:
+
+```bash
+npx netlify dev
+```
+
+Run a passive homepage scan:
+
+```bash
+npm run scan -- --url https://example.com --out ./scan-output/example
+```
+
+Generate local drafts only after setting a real sender name, valid postal address, HTTPS deployment URL, and reviewed input:
+
+```bash
+SENDER_FULL_NAME="Real Name" \
+BUSINESS_POSTAL_ADDRESS="Valid postal address" \
+PUBLIC_SITE_URL="https://your-site.netlify.app" \
+npm run outreach:draft -- ./templates/prospect-batch.example.json ./outreach/drafts/batch.json
+```
+
+Commercial sending is disabled by default. The Apps Script sender requires `ALLOW_COMMERCIAL_SEND=true` in Netlify, `ALLOW_COMMERCIAL_SEND=TRUE` in Apps Script, a real sender identity, a valid postal address, a monitored mailbox, and a staff-approved database row. It never approves its own drafts.
+
+## Deployment order
+
+1. Create or connect a **clean Supabase project dedicated to AccessRevamp**.
+2. Apply the three migrations in `supabase/migrations/` in filename order.
+3. Configure Supabase Auth URLs and create the first staff user.
+4. Connect this repository to Netlify, assign the generated `*.netlify.app` URL, and configure environment variables.
+5. Configure the existing Stripe sandbox catalog prices, webhook, and restricted API key; then complete the test matrix.
+6. Add a real monitored contact email, truthful sender identity, and valid postal address.
+7. Complete the launch checklist before taking live payments or considering an email provider.
+
+Detailed instructions are in [`docs/deployment/LAUNCH-CHECKLIST.md`](docs/deployment/LAUNCH-CHECKLIST.md).
+
+## Non-negotiable boundaries
+
+- Automated tools do not determine accessibility by themselves. Prospect-facing findings must be manually verified.
+- Review public pages only. Do not log in, submit forms, test checkout, create accounts, bypass controls, evade rate limits, or perform active vulnerability testing.
+- Use **severity** and **confidence**, not unsupported security claims.
+- Do not promise legal compliance, certification, zero risk, or guaranteed business results.
+- Use only appropriate business contacts the company publishes itself, record the source URL, honor opt-outs permanently, and contact no other employee to evade an objection.
+- AI may explain, prioritize, and draft. A human remains responsible for the finding, concept, recipient, and message.
+
+## Current activation status
+
+The codebase is complete and testable locally. Stripe sandbox products and one-time prices are provisioned. It is not live until a dedicated Supabase project is connected, Netlify environment configuration and the Stripe webhook are completed, and a real business contact identity is supplied. See [`BUILD_STATUS.md`](BUILD_STATUS.md) for exact blockers.
